      "content": "it’s just hard to see the \"value\" when everything feels so mechanical and cold. like we're just biological machines waiting to malfunction. every day is just a repetition of the same empty cycles. if the universe doesn't care and there's no bigger purpose, then isn't it just more rational to stop trying to force a meaning that isn't there?",
